    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-grade example of sequential twin-turbocharged engineering. The 13B-REW rotary power plant exhibits stellar compression across all rotor faces, ensuring the Hitachi HT12 turbos spool linearly through the transition point without hesitation. The drivetrain features the original five-speed manual transmission paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential, delivering power to a chassis that retains its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and 50/50 weight distribution. Meticulously preserved with a pristine vacuum line rack and zero thermal fatigue on the cooling system, this R1-package-inspired build offers the tactile feedback and high-revving performance of a true JDM icon in its purest form.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 15
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Mint condition. Zero mechanical issues. Flawless interior and exterior. Clean title. Single owner.",
